			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2008</a> paper:</span><br><i>Neon: A Library for Language Usage Analysis</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/JurriaanHage.html">Jurriaan Hage</a>, <a href="../profile/PetervanKeeken.html">Peter van Keeken</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_4">10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_4</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It presents a reusable library/tooling infrastructure for analyzing how a language is used in practice.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5b.html"><span class="tagL">T5B: Language Description Analysis</span></a><ul><li> Its purpose is to support language-oriented analysis by extracting and aggregating usage information.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2b.html"><span class="tagL">T2B: Evolution</span></a><ul><li> The usage-analysis capability is motivated as feedback for evolving and maintaining languages and their ecosystems.
</li></ul></li></ul>
